I have started and coached a new FIRST Robotics Competition  team last year for 2014-2015 season and wanted to use Java. Initially I thought the programming would be very complicated for the high school students, many of whom didn&#x27;t have any prior programming experience.<p>How can you control the speed of the robot proportional to the pressure applied on the joystick for example?. However, I was very pleased with the WPILib framework that comes with the kit. This can be accomplished by essentially a single  line like (ignoring the variable initialization),<p><pre><code>    myRobot.arcade(stick);
</code></pre>
